column19: Welcome to our Commit Message Evaluation Survey!This survey should take up to 20 minutes to answer. You will be given 15 commit URLs (which enables you to gain required context about the commit) and two candidate commit messages for those commits. For each commit URL we will ask you to select the superior commit message based on four evaluation criteria. Below are the evaluation criteria and their definitions: Rationality reflects whether the commit message provides a logical explanation for the code change (Why information) and provides the commit type information.Comprehensiveness reflects whether the message describes a summary of what has been changed (What information) and also covers details (i.e. whether the commit message fails relevant imports to describe the code changes in a changed file.)Conciseness indicates whether the message conveys information succinctly ensuring readability and quick comprehension.Expressiveness reflects whether the message content is grammatically correct and fluent.Additionally for each commit you are asked to select your overall preferred commit message.If you need to review these criteria at any point in questions you may click on the small question icon to show up the criteria.
